<div class="container container--marketing container--marketingLight">
  <div class="container container--fixedWidth container--forContent">
    <h2>Stop doing QA in the dark</h2>
    <h3>See every pixel change before launch</h3>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="one-third column">
        <p>
          <strong>Go beyond unit testing.</strong>
        </p>
        <p>
          With one line of code, Percy snapshots your UI and shows you exactly what pixels changed from the last time.
        </p>
        <p>
          <code style="padding: 10px">
            Percy.snapshot(page)
          </code>
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Avoid expensive and error-prone manual QA.</strong> Get visibility into exactly how code visually changes your app.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="two-thirds column">
        <p>
          <img style="width: 125%" src="/images/example-diff.png">
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="container container--marketing container--marketing">
  <div class="container container--fixedWidth container--forContent">
    <h2>CI friendly</h2>
    <h3>Plays nice in your environment</h3>
    <p class="u-text-center">
      <img src="/images/github-success-flyout.png">
    </p>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="one-half column">
        <p>
          <strong>Automatically integrates with GitHub Pull Requests.</strong>
          If any visual diffs are found, you simply review them and click <i>Approve</i> to make the build green.
        </p>
        <p>
          Percy was also designed from the ground up to be <strong>compatible with any CI environment</strong>
          and even local development. If there is HTML and CSS, Percy will work.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="one-half column u-text-center">
        <img src="/images/cis.png">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
